{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require building of fully wheelchair accessible homes in all new developments",
        "additional_details": "\u2022 Make wheelchair accessible (Category 3) homes a mandatory requirement in all new housing developments\r\n\u2022 Set a national minimum percentage of wheelchair accessible homes for every development\r\n\u2022 Strengthen and enforce building regulations so developers cannot opt out of accessibility requirements\r\n\u2022 Increase investment in accessible social housing\r\n\u2022 Create a national accessible housing register\r\n\u2022 Improve funding and processes for home adaptations",
        "background": "We believe accessible housing isn't a luxury & is essential for independent living & equal participation in society. The UK cannot meet the obligations of the Equality Act or the UN Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities without addressing the crisis of a lack of accessible housing.",
